item.title: Ehrharta erecta var. erecta
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: 2nd pic shows flowers. This is a serious weed. Taking over areas and easily spread by Council graders on dirt roads. Seed are enjoyed by seed-eating birds including finches and crimson rosellas.

item.title: Linum trigynum
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Many thousands of plants at this site. Mostly single-stemmed and upright but occasionally multi-stemmed and ascending stems on plants one foot wide. Flowers very small, same size as Cicendia and Sebaea.
